    <article class="Writing__client">
      <div class="Writing__logo">
        <%= image_tag "logos/doc-halo.png", :class => "Image--full", :title => "Doc Halo", :alt => "Doc Halo" %>
      </div>
      <div class="Writing__description">
        <p>
          Doc Halo is a messaging app that allows medical professionals to safety text and share patient data with one another in a clinical setting while following HIPAA compliance. In the past, doctors have used pagers and phones for this purpose, so this product is truly the wave of the future for hospitals and medical centers, especially since mobile devices are becoming ubiquitous in the workplace. I’ve always been known as a health writer, but this client was especially rewarding because I got to write about the space where health meets tech - a burgeoning industry with lots of potential.
        </p>
        <p>
          The client wanted to inform patients about what the modern hospital workplace looks like and could be, and wanted to give important updates about health IT advancements. Since many of the end readers were healthcare professionals, I incorporated an informative yet edgy voice in order to increase brand awareness and optimize user experience.
        </p>
      </div>
      <ul class="Writing__links">
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.dochalo.com/blog/4-things-to-include-in-a-hospital-byod-policy" target="_blank">4 things to include in a hospital BYOD policy</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.dochalo.com/blog/implementation-and-adoption-best-practices-for-healthcare-technology" target="_blank">Implementation and adoption: Best practices for healthcare technology</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.dochalo.com/blog/steps-for-improving-doctor-to-nurse-communication" target="_blank">Steps for improving doctor-to-nurse communication</a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.dochalo.com/blog/the-importance-of-streamlined-patient-handoff" target="_blank">4 things to include in a hospital BYOD policy</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="Writing__client">
      <div class="Writing__logo">
        <%= image_tag "logos/lovely.png", :class => "Image--full", :title => "Lovely", :alt => "Lovely" %>
      </div>
      <div class="Writing__description">
        <p>
          Lovely is a part of the RentPath family, and is a platform that connects renters to their potential new home. The client specifically wanted to appeal to a millennial audience, so many of the pieces needed to address and attract end users who were new to the rental market or simply relocating with little knowledge of the rental market.
        </p>
        <p>
          This was a fun blog to write for because the content was very “voicey” and I was given free reign to interject many of my own real-life experiences with the rental market (the good, the bad and the ugly), making it a very worthwhile experience.
        </p>
      </div>
      <ul class="Writing__links">
        <li>
